Naspers Chairman Says Global Economy Discouraging Consumers, Advertisers

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-08-26T09:36:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-26/naspers-chairman-says-global-economy-discouraging-consumers-advertisers.html
Naspers Ltd. (NPN)  has processes in place
to help mitigate the effects of global economic risks, Chairman
Ton Vosloo told investors at the company’s annual general
meeting in  Cape Town  today.  The global economy is “difficult to read” at the moment,
he said, and the “general atmosphere of stagnation” doesn’t
encourage consumers or advertisers to spend money.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Brand in Cape Town at 
 rbrand9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  